DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20260420T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Chicago:20260420T143000
SUMMARY:Annual Meeting and Program: Songs for Spring
DESCRIPTION:Alliance Française du North Shore\n**Annual Meeting for Alliance Française Members**\nRequired by Alliance Française du North Shore bylaws\, this short members' meeting will convene at approximately 2:15 PM\, immediately following the monthly program. This meeting will include approval of the proposed 2026-2027 budget and the election of members of the board of directors. Members of the AFduNS as of April 1 are eligible to vote in the election and on other matters.\n\nIf you're unable to attend the annual meeting\, please complete this proxy ballot (link to come) **by 10 AM on Monday\, April 20**.\n\n**Program**\nSinger and guitarist Kevin Soucie returns to share his extensive repertoire\, including songs by Jacques Brel\, Édith Piaf\, Charles Trenet\, Francis Cabrel\, Charles Aznavour and many others. This intimate performance will transport you to the cafés of Paris with timeless melodies. [Click here for the program selections.](https://storage.googleapis.com/production-ipage-v1-0-0/830/1512830/9C8FaW1X/5b3eb831f2be4f27a020c51e7e705663?fileName=Music%20Program%202026.pdf) You won’t be able to help but sing along.\n\nKevin Soucie travels the country performing timeless\, popular and contemporary French songs for francophone audiences. A native of Milwaukee\, Soucie was a student in Québec and in Europe\, and also served as a Peace Corps volunteer in Senegal. Hearing French and Québecois songs along the way\, Soucie was inspired to sing and play *chansons* with his guitar—a hobby that became a passion.\n\n**Program Registration for Members of the AF DuPage: Free**\nIf you're a member of the AF DuPage and are attending a monthly program for the first time\, please RSVP to programmes@AFnorthshore.org with “DuPage” in the subject line. Include your name and Zoom screen name\, if different. If you're a member of our Meetup group\, we'll mark you as such and you'll no longer need to send RSVP emails as long as you RSVP on Meetup.\nIf you're not a member of the AFduNS Meetup group\, you'll need to send an email RSVP for each monthly program.\n\n**Program Registration for Nonmembers: $10**\nIf you're not a member of the AFduNS or the AF DuPage\, the cost of attending this program is $10. [Click here](https://forms.gle/f89WGYhPkj867tYi8) to register and pay online with PayPal by 8 PM the day before the program. There will be no refunds or credits.\n\nWe appreciate reservations by 8 PM the day before the program. Walk-ins may pay at the door on their mobile device.\n\n**Membership in the AFduNS**\nWhile no membership is required for newcomers\, we welcome new members whose membership will support the activities of the AFduNS\, a nonprofit 501(c)(3) organization. For further info\, visit our [website](https://afnorthshore.org/events) or [click here to contact us](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScRxM03DpryO_lZlGWK-aDOCiFHFbivJimTScMOQmWk7KgOJQ/viewform?pli=1). If you wish to join the AFduNS\, you may sign up [online](https://afnorthshore.org/join). Annual dues are $50.00.
